<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870220-0047 </DOCNO><HL> GTE Unit Wins$870.6 MillionArmy Contract</HL><DD> 02/20/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> GTE ITT KAMNA IBM LIT HPC ALDAEROSPACE (ARO)DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   GTE Government Systems Corp., a unit of GTE Corp., received an $870.6 million Army contract for mobile battlefield-communications equipment.    About three-quarters of the work will be done in the continental U.S., with the rest in Canada. The new award is a modification of a 1984 contract and is to be completed in December 1993.    In other awards yesterday, ITT Corp. won a $53.9 million Navy contract for electronic circuit switches.    Kaman Aerospace Corp., a unit of Kaman Corp., was issued a $42.3 million Navy contract for SH-2F helicopters.    International Business Machines Corp. received $30.1 million Navy contract to produce signal processors.    Units of Litton Industries Inc. were awarded contracts totaling $21.3 million for maintenance of a guided-missile cruiser for the Navy and for aircraft parts for the Air Force.    Israel Aircraft Industries Ltd. received an $18.8 million Navy contract for S-21A aircraft maintenance.    Hercules Inc. won a $14.7 million Army contract to operate a munitions plant at Desota, Kan.    Allied-Signal Inc. received a $13.7 million Navy contract for aircraft electronic equipment. </TEXT></DOC>